explanations.description: Prefixes indicating various concepts, often used to convey meaning related to position, size, quantity, or direction, such as "uni-" (one), "pos-" (position), "neg-" (negative), "ant-" (against), "pro-" (for), "eco-" (ecological), "soci-" (social), "phys-" (physical), "comb-" (combative), "con-" (together), or "sen-" (senate), among others, and also used in various words like "testable", "passable", "punish", "competitive", "pollution", "logistically", " senatorial", "brown nosing", "combative", " cribbing", "defeat", and "moderator".
